  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Iron-Father Gdolkin is pulled away from the defence of Medusa to honour an ancient oath sworn to the Adeptus Mechanicus, and a trail through the Mechanicus archives draws him to a long-lost world that may hold a weapon capable of turning the tide of Abaddon's 13th Black Crusade. The same lost world is rumoured to hide the resting place of Ferrus Manus, primarch of the Iron Hands — the oldest mystery of the chapter — and the quest curdles into something personal. Written from inside the chapter's machine-supremacist register: a Mechanicus-theological quest novel.",
